      "content": "While maintaining consistent levels can sometimes be beneficial for certain conditions, managing pain with over-the-counter medication requires care. Taking standard doses too frequently, even if it seems logical, can lead to exceeding the maximum safe daily limit. For lower back pain, it is crucial to check the specific \"every 4 to 6 hours\" guideline on your packaging to avoid potential side effects from overuse. Please use the label instructions as a guide until you can speak with a qualified healthcare professional.",
